SIMPLE: nominalize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nominalize
<hw>Nom"i*nal*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <fld>(Grammar,
Linguistics)</fld> <def>To convert into a noun; <as>as, a
<ex>nominalized</ex> sentence; a <ex>nominalized</ex> adjective or
verb</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>In a sentence of the form:⟦br⟧
⟦ldquo⟧That Kennedy would have been a great president if he had not been
assassinated is one of the enduring myths of the Camelot
conceit.⟦rdquo⟧⟦br⟧
the sentence ⟦ldquo⟧Kennedy would have been a great president if he had
not been assassinated⟦rdquo⟧ has been <ex>nominalized</ex> by the
introductory ⟦ldquo⟧that⟦rdquo⟧.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nominally</ent>⟦br⟧
